D=774.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Updated suggestions on Magician Pet Heals...</span><hr size=1> Since we found out about Refresh Summoning and the new Planar Renewal pet heals I decided to do a fast rehash of all the old and new pet heals, comparing their efficiency and pointing out the problems with some of the heals. For the reason compared between the statistics of the level 20 pet heal and the new level 64 pet heal, the rest seems rather unbalanced (underpowered) and out of scale. This was a reply to another thread, but the nature of this issue made me reevualuate that and I decided to make this into a new thread instead.<br>
<br>
The level 20 pet heal had a 2.25 h/m ratio, this is 1.9 h/m. In short I would not use this spell, I would stick with the level 20 pet heal until you get the level 60 pet heal, with THAT ratio is not very good either...2.2 h/m ratio. The only reason I use the level 60 pet heal is the fact it is no worse than the level 20 pet heal, but it is also no better. I avoided use of the level 52 pet heal altogether when I got it. But the new planar pet heal is REAL nice at a 4.0 h/m ratio. They just need to scale the other pet heals accordingly.<br>
<br>
Here are the pet heals (OLD and NEW)...<br>
<br>
LV8: Renew Elements<br>
Increase Hit Points (HP) from 33 (L8 )  to 50 (L25) for 25 mana. (MAX 2.0 h/m ratio)<br>
LV20: Renew Summoning<br>
Increase Hit Points (HP) from 140 (L20) to 220 (L60) for 100 mana. (MAX 2.25 h/m ratio)<br>
LV44: Refresh Summoning*<br>
Increase Hit Points (HP) from 338 (L44) to 370 (L60) for 200 mana. (MAX 1.85 h/m ratio)<br>
LV52: Transon's Elemental Infusion<br>
Increase Hit Points (HP) from 556 (L52) to 580 (L60) for 275 mana. (MAX 2.11 h/m ratio)<br>
LV60: Transon's Elemental Renewal<br>
Increase Hit Points (HP) by 900 (L60) for 400 mana. (MAX 2.25 h/m ratio)<br>
LV64: Planar Renewal**<br>
Increase Hit Points (HP) by 1200 (L64) for 300 mana. (MAX 4.0 h/m ratio)<br>
<br>
*Denotes a spell of unknown origin, this may be a POP spell or may not.<br>
**Denotes a POP spell.<br>
<br>
As you can see here only the level 8 and level 20 pet heals scaled correctly. But the other 3 pet heals do not, it was not until POP that we (so far) get a truly improved pet heal in Planar Renewel. The Level 44 and 52 pet heals are actually WORSE in their heal to mana ratios. But based on the level 20 pet heals and the new POP pet heal I do have suggestions on what the lv44, 52, and lv60 pet heals should look like, without changing how much they heal.<br>
<br>
*Change MAG LV44 Refresh Summoning from a mana cost 200 to a mana cost of 150. This changes the mana ratio from 1.85 h/m to a ratio of 2.47 h/m.<br>
*Change MAG LV52 Transon's Elemental Infusion from a mana cost of 275 to a mana cost of 200. This changes the mana ratio from 2.11 h/m to a ratio of 2.9 h/m.<br>
*Change MAG LV60 Transon's Elemental Renewal from a mana cost of 400 to a mana cost of 260. This changes the mana ratio from a 2.25 h/m to a ratio of 3.46 h/m.<br>
<br>
From these new numbers you would see a general linear increase in the spell performance from the old pet heal spell at level 20 to the new pet heal at level 64. As the level 44, 52, and 60 pet heals stand, they are unbalanced and out of scale and do need retroactive changing to reflect the old and new heal.<br>
<br>
The GameMaster...<br>
<br>
Mystis Zephyr, Level 60 Master of the Elements Arch Mage of the Test Realm...<br>
<br>
