<br>
Changing the older pet heals to reflect that scale between what the level 20 pet heal is and level 64 pet heal would still not make us anywhere near as good as a pet healer as beastlords currently are. There pet heals have FAR better mana ratios and can be cast a lot faster and does not have a recast like our pet heals do. Also remember in the comparisons you was making that Beastlords also have access to Spell Haste items and Mana Preservation items. The only things they do not have access to is specialization and spell casting mastery. But if you feel this way WEZLOC, are you recommending that they remove or reduce the power of not only our current pet heals but Planar renewal as well?<br>
<br>
You have not explained to me why they should NOT rebalance the older Magician pet heals or why they should reduce (nerf) the power of the older pet heals. But like I said earlier...rebalancing the older level 44, 52, and 60 pet heals has nothing to do with your post. This thread was only about rebalancing and rescaling the older MAGICIAN pet heals and was not even looking at the beastlord pet heals for a comparision. But if you do wish to compare the spells then it stands the magician pet heals seem more unbalanced when compared to the Beastlord class. Regardless it does stand that the older pet heals are INDEED unbalanced as is and out of scale.<br>
<br>
The GameMaster...<br>
