<br>
A few quick questions regarding one class 'encroaching' on another's territory.<br>
<br>
1. Why should a hybrid be better at any casting skill than a pure caster? <br>
<br>
2. Can you name any example of where another hybrid is better at a 'type' of spell than their pure caster brethren?<br>
<br>
3. Does a self only, or self-pet only ability do anything to increase a class's desirability in groups or on raids?<br>
<br>
4. Now that BL's can effectively chain summon warders, why should it matter if we come close to them in healing power?<br>
<br>
5. Beastlord's have many deficiencies, how does a better mage pet only heal make a difference to beastlords?<br>
<br>
I guess where I'm leading with these questions is that it should make no difference to the BL's if mages become better pet clerics, as it has no impact on their desirability in groups or on raids. This isn't exactly the same thing as druids and shammies getting versions of CH..... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
There's no reason the beastlord's can't continue to receive other upgrades without mage heals becoming better as well.<br>
<br>
That being said, I think VI should decide on a pet healing ratio for mages. At a minimum, that ratio should stay the same for each of the subsequent spells, possibly getting a little better as you progress later in the game. Naturally this ratio should be improved from where it currently stands.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cp. <p>Naladini <BR>
Elementalist of the 54th Season-Stormhammer<BR>
