<br>
I don't agree. SCM3 can be had at level 55. From that point forward a mage can start drastically reducing his mana cost in his given specialization. I think to ignore that is foolish. Beastlords are a support pet class, i.e. the term pet cleric.  Mages have ALWAYS been Wizard with a pet model. We have a very low cost pet that can be replaced for little cost. That is a huge advantage for the mage.  <br>
<br>
I just think that bst were made with the intent of being the best healing pet class. They heal the best so there pet is alot weaker. If we start healing as good as they do then there is no reason their pets should not be stronger relative to ours. Considering that we are gonna be able to do near 280dps with 1 nuke and they can barely scratch 50dps even uber. At some point the mage has to give up something. We are the best pet class that doesn't mean we should be equal in healing also. We have the strongest pets and they are the easiest to replace, vs a  class that has weaker pets, which are more difficult to replace.  <br>
<br>
If a mage can do double the dps of a bst, and his pet can do double the dps of a warder then the beastlord has to have a advantage somewhere. Right now it is utility i.e. personal heals, slow and pet heals. Remember bst do not get root or snare just like mages. They are a hybrid pet class that pays the same penalty for having a good pet as a mage. Instead of snare they get slow. The reason they heal better then a mage is because they are part priest.  I think pushing for better heals is a very tricky territory. If you want better heals you have to give up something for them. I personally don't want to give up anymore to other classes.<br>
<br>
I soloed Yeldema with only the level 52 pet heal and finished the fight with mana. I solo in UP daily and net 3/4 blue per kill. I think the heals serve the mage just fine if he knows what he is doing. We always bitch as a class that druids shouldn't be able to heal almost as good as a cleric and nuke almost as good as a wizard. Well we see how unfair it is that druids are so overpowered. Why do you want the same for us?<br>
